Bragdoc is a powerful command-line interface (CLI) tool designed to help individuals
build their own "Brag Documents" to track and showcase their professional achievements.

Usage:
  bragdoc [command]

Available Commands:
  brag        Manage your brag entries
  completion  Generate the autocompletion script for the specified shell
  doc         Generate brag documents
  help        Help about any command
  init        Initialize Bragdoc configuration and database
  tag         Manage tags for organizing brags
  version     Print the version number of Bragdoc

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for bragdoc

Use "bragdoc [command] --help" for more information about a command.
